# Poke Express TS

Poke Express TS is a typescript based project with an own logger.

## Installation

For running it locally (macOS), you must have this main resources installed:
- [Node](https://nodejs.org/en/download/current)
- [NVM](https://github.com/nvm-sh/nvm?tab=readme-ov-file#installing-and-updating) (recommended)
- [Yarn](https://classic.yarnpkg.com/lang/en/docs/install/#mac-stable)

## Usage

For common usage:

```sh
# sets node version to expected one
nvm install

# installs all necessary dependencies
yarn install

# runs project locally on port 8000
yarn dev
```

If you want to mess up with log levels, default is `ERROR`, but you can always use the other ones:

```sh
# WARN
yarn dev-warn

# INFO
yarn dev-info

# DEBUG
yarn dev-debug

# TRACE
yarn dev-trace
```
